}, and {{p|Tsareena}}. They are all known as the Fruit Pokémon.\n* Of all the Pokémon that existed during [[Generation IV]], Tropius is the only one that is exclusive to {{v2|Platinum}}.\n\n===Origin===\nTropius resembles a generic {{wp|sauropoda|sauropod}}, a long-necked, herbivorous {{wp|dinosaur}}, combined with a {{wp|banana}} plant.\n\n====Name origin====\nTropius is a combination of \'\'tropical\'\' and \'\'saurus\'\' (Greek for \'\'lizard\'\'). It may also be a pun of \'\'tropism\'\': {{wp|phototropism}} is when plants move to catch more sunlight, and if a plant is not planted upright, the roots will use {{wp|gravitropism}} to grow towards gravity and find water.\n\n==In other languages==\n{{Other languages|type=Grass|type2=Flying\n|ja=トロピウス \'\'Tropius\'\'|jameaning=From \'\'tropical\'\', \'\'{{tt|saurus|Greek for lizard}}\'\', and possibly \'\'tropism\'\'\n|fr=Tropius|frmeaning=Same as English name\n|es=Tropius|esmeaning=Same as English name\n|de=Tropius|demeaning=Same as English name\n|it=Tropius|itmeaning=Same as English name\n|ko=트로피우스 \'\'Tropius\'\'|komeaning=Transliteration of Japanese name\n|zh_cmn=熱帶龍 / 热带龙 \'\'Rèdàilóng\'\'|zh_cmnmeaning=Literally "Tropical dragon"\n|hi=ट्रोपियस \'\'Tropius\'\'|himeaning=Transliteration of English name\n}}\n{{left clear}}\n\n==Related articles==\n* [[Troppy]]\n\n==External links==\n\n{{-}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Head|type=Grass|type2=Flying}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Pokémon|type=Grass|prevnum=356|prev=Dusclops|nextnum=358|next=Chimecho}}\n|}\n{{Project Pokédex notice}}\n\n[[Category:Shadow Pokémon in Pokémon Colosseum]]\n\n[[de:Tropius]]\n[[es:Tropius]]\n[[fr:Tropius]]\n[[it:Tropius]]\n[[ja:トロピウス]]\n[[zh:热带龙]]'}